# EmailJS Configuration for OTP Email Sending
# =============================================
# Follow these steps to enable real OTP emails via your Google account:
#
# 1. Go to https://www.emailjs.com/ and sign up for free
# 2. Click "Add New Service" → select Gmail → connect your Google account
# 3. Copy the Service ID (e.g., service_abc123)
# 4. Go to "Email Templates" → "Create New Template"
#    Use these template variables in your email body:
#      Subject: Your OTP Code - Pass The Paper
#      Body: Hello {{user_name}}, your OTP is: {{otp_code}}. Expires in {{expiry_minutes}} minutes.
# 5. Copy the Template ID (e.g., template_xyz789)
# 6. Go to "Account" → "General" → copy your Public Key
# 7. Rename this file to .env and fill in your values below:

VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=your_service_id_here
VITE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=your_template_id_here
VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=your_public_key_here
VITE_API_URL=https://passthepaperspringboot-production.up.railway.app

# NOTE: EmailJS free plan allows 200 emails/month which is fine for testing.
# In dev mode (without these keys), OTP codes are logged to the browser console.
